  "input": "Hospitalization report\nThis is the patient BENDJELIDA ISRAA, aged 14, originally from and residing in ORAN, from a non-consanguineous middle-aged couple, followed at our level since December 2011 for cystic fibrosis with double respiratory and digestive phenotypic expression on the homozygous genetic mutation. F508del; Admitted to our department on 03/24/2026 for an exacerbation of his illness. HISTORY:\nFamily:\n-Father: aged 62 in BES. -Mother: aged 42; in BES. -Consanguinity: no\n-Siblings: Brother aged 09 known from service for cystic fibrosis. Child died at 03 days of life due to lack of meconium emission. Personal:\nPhysiological\n-Pregnancy: Well monitored\n-Term birth by vaginal route. -Apgar 7/10 then 09/10\n-Birth weight: 03kg300, Height (51 cm), BW (34 cm)\n-Meconium emitted <24 hours, no notion of neonatal jaundice\n- Breastfeeding: Exclusive maternal until the age of 4 months then artificial\n-Diversification started at the age of 6 months\n-Vaccination: CORRECT\n-Psychomotor development: GOOD\n-Schooling: 4th AM, good academic performance. Diagnostic elements:\nAnamnestic:\nConcept of delayed meconium emission. Death of a brother at the age of 3 days (no meconium emission). Brother aged 09 known for cystic fibrosis. Clinic:\nChronic cough since the age of 1 month\nBronchial congestion from the age of 2 months\nChronic oily diarrhea from the age of 2 months\nParaclinic:\n-Positive sweat test:\n1st Test on 02/11/2011\n(Right forearm) 262 mg (sweat weight) 90 meq/l (chlorine level)\n02nd Test 11/29/2011 (Right forearm) 216 mg 93 meq/l\n- Genetic study: 01/31/2012: homozygous mutation p.F508del\n-Fecal elastase 03/26/2025: 1.8ug/ exocrine pancreatic insufficiency\nProcessing in progress:\n-For respiratory purposes:\nRespiratory physiotherapy at home twice daily\nHypertonic nebulization\nNebulization with Colistin twice a day every other month\n- For nutritional purposes:\nCreon 12000 IU (520 IU/Kg)\nVit K 10 mg/15 days\nVit D amp/3 months\nVit E 1cp/d\nTherapeutic compliance: Good\nHISTORY OF ILLNESS: related to the reason for hospitalization: 03/24/2026\nThe beginning of the signs dates back 15 days previously with accentuation of the cough becoming annoying, modification of the sputum which has become greenish and thick, with asthenia and reduction in appetite hence its admission. CLINICAL EXAMINATION UPON ADMISSION: Date: 03/24/2026\n• Anthropometric measurements:\nWeight: 45,800 kg (-0.81 DS). Height: 162 cm (+0.15 DS). BMI:17.5 kg/m2 (-1.04 SD). Eutrophic child\n• Average general condition, febrile: T: 40.1° C, mild malnutrition. • Skin examination: Pale skin, no jaundice or hemorrhagic syndrome. • ENT examination: allergic rhinitis\n• Pleuropulmonary examination: FR: 18 c/, fits of wet cough, auscultation, bilateral rumbling rales, vesicular murmurs well transmitted in 2 pulmonary fields. - No signs of struggle, Spo2: 97% under AA. - Signs of chronic respiratory failure (clubbing + Pectus Excavatum chest deformity)\n• Cardiovascular examination: HR: 88b/min. Auscultation: no breathing or BSA, heart sounds were clearly audible. • Examination of the abdomen, distended soft abdomen, 01 to 02 soft fatty stools, no signs of dehydration, free hernia orifices, no rectal prolapse. • Reduced appetite, disturbed sleep. • Preserved diuresis. • Examination of other devices without particularity. PARACLINICAL ASSESSMENT UPON ADMISSION: 10/28/25\nCBC: Coagulated blood\nTP: 69.6% TQ: 15.6 Sec TCK: 33Sec\nCRP: 7.9mg/l (negative). PCT: < 0.05 ng/ml (negative)\nBlood ionogram (normal): Na: 138.9 mmol/l K: 3.89 mmol/l Cl: 102 mmol/l\nLiver test (normal): AST: 11U/l gGT: 17.57 LDH: 333 U/L\nBlood sugar: 0.97 g/L (normal). TG: 1.25 g/l (normal). Magnesemia: 21.95 ml (normal). Calcemia: 97.2 mg/L (normal)\nAlbumin: 38g/l (normal). Creat: 5.02 mg/l (normal). Urea: 0.12 g/l (normal). Total Protein: 69.3 g/l (normal)\nFerritin: 2.1 ng/ml (low). 25 OH Vit D: 28.3 ng/ml (slight deficiency)\nSUPPORT:\nOn the respiratory level\nNebulization with SSH before respiratory physiotherapy. Twice-daily respiratory physiotherapy\nBi IV antibiotic therapy:\nFortum 200mg/kg/day. Amikacin 25 mg/kg/day IV for 10 days. Zomax 1 day/2 days\nNutritionally:\nInterview with the dietitian. Growth curve.\nPolyvitamin supplementation: {vitamin D/2 months Vit K/15days Vit E/15days} and iron deficiency. Creon 12000 iu 01 capsule 10/d\nVenofer infusion. Evolution during hospitalization:\nRegression of signs of struggle with complete disappearance of cough and reduction in the volume of sputum. The Child stayed for 13 days having received Bi antibiotic therapy: Fortum for 13 days, Amikacin for 10 days with venofer infusion 3 times at 3 day intervals and vitamin supplementation. OUTLINE AND FOCUS OF THE DISEASE:\nOn the respiratory level:\nSign of chronic respiratory failure “clubbing + Thoracic deformity”\nNo signs of chronic cor pulmonale. Heart echo (05/04//2026): without anomaly\nEFR (01-12-24):\nFEV 63% FEV/FVC 112%\nFVC 57% DEP 90 L/sec\nDecrease in all proximal and distal flow rates, restrictive ventilatory deficit\nECBC of sputum: 03/29/2026: Absence of germs (after course of antibiotics). Arterial blood gas: 06/16/25: Normal ph: 7.434 po2:91 mm hg pco2 39.5 mm hg\nThoracic CT 01/2025: Bilateral cystic dilatation of the bronchi with thickening of the bronchial walls, Right inter-bronchial mediatisnal lymphadenopathy of 11mm. On the hemodynamic level\nNo signs of heart failure (no edema or hepatosplenomegaly, or turgidity of the jugulars. No signs of chronic cor pulmonale. Heart echo 04/05/2026: Without abnormalities. On the digestive and hepatobiliary level:\nNo jaundice, no notion of digestive bleeding, hepatomegaly. Absence of constipation,\nAbsence of rectal prolapse. Correct liver test: AST: 11U/l gGT: 17.57 LDH: 333 U/L\nAbdominopelvic ultrasound 04/06/2026: Homogeneous hepato-splenomegaly without detectable nodular lesion. Free intraperitoneal effusion of moderate abundance. Simple left ovarian cyst of 36mm. Nutritionally and metabolically:\nWeight: 45,800 kg (-0.81 DS). Height: 162 cm (+0.15 DS). BMI:17.5 kg/m2 (-1.04 SD). No weight loss. Preserved daily ration\nBlood sugar: 0.80 g/l HbA1C (12/24/2025): 6.30%. Correct nutritional assessment except hypovitaminosis D and hypoferritinemia\nFerritin: 2.1 ng/ml 25 OH Vit D: 28.3 ng/ml\nNormal growth curve. On the ENT level:\nNasal obstruction, rhinorrhea\nCT of the sinuses (03-23-2025): maxillo-sphenoethmoidal sinusitis (very dense content),\nCONCLUSION:\nThe child Bendjlida Israa aged 14, originally from and residing in Oran, from a non-consanguineous couple, followed since the age of 3 months for cystic fibrosis with dual respiratory and digestive phenotypic expression, readmitted for moderate exacerbation of cystic fibrosis which had progressed well under treatment. Child discharged after good clinical and biological progress with control appointment on 07/07/2026\nTo collect / To do:\n- Thoracic CT with injection\n- ECBC with antibiogram\n- Plan an HbA1C with OGTT\n- Provide aspergillus serology\n- Plan a nighttime saturation curve for the next hospitalization\n- Referral to ENT\nResident of the department: Dr Djoudi Assistant of the department: Dr OUSSALAH",
